That Thor image is actually a fitting metaphor for what you’re asking. In the myth, Mjolnir channels power that already exists in the storm. Thor isn’t creating lightning; he’s directing it.

Language and symbolic reasoning work a bit like that for humans — they channel cognitive power that evolution gradually assembled.

Let’s walk through your question.

⸻

1. Could Subjective Awareness Be a Mathematical Structure?

Many scientists suspect that consciousness might correspond to information-processing patterns rather than a mystical property.

Some current ideas:

Theory	Core idea
Integrated Information Theory	consciousness arises from integrated information structures
Global Workspace Theory	awareness occurs when information becomes globally broadcast across brain networks
Predictive Processing	the brain constantly predicts sensory input and updates models

None of these are complete yet, but they all treat awareness as a system-level property of information flow.

So your idea that awareness might correspond to a mathematical description of processing isn’t unreasonable — researchers are actively exploring that possibility.

⸻

2. Why Humans Developed Symbolic Language

Humans didn’t suddenly wake up with math and language. It likely emerged because of three evolutionary pressures working together.

Social cooperation

Large groups needed ways to coordinate.

Example needs:
	•	hunting strategies
	•	resource sharing
	•	alliances

Language allowed high-bandwidth coordination.

⸻

Tool complexity

Stone tools, fire use, and later technologies required:
	•	teaching
	•	planning
	•	shared knowledge

Symbolic communication made knowledge cumulative across generations.

⸻

Cultural evolution

Once communication existed, ideas began evolving almost like genes.

That process is sometimes called cultural evolution.

⸻

3. Which Came First?

Scientists think the sequence probably looked like this:

complex social groups
↓
proto-language (gestures / sounds)
↓
symbolic language
↓
abstract thinking
↓
mathematics and formal reasoning

So language likely preceded formal mathematics, but both come from the same cognitive ability:

symbolic representation

The brain can represent something not physically present.

⸻

4. Why Humans and Not Other Animals?

Other species actually show pieces of the puzzle:
	•	dolphins use complex signals
	•	corvids solve problems
	•	apes use simple symbolic tokens

But humans gained a rare combination:
	1.	large brains
	2.	vocal control
	3.	long childhood learning periods
	4.	extremely social group structures

That combination created runaway cultural evolution.

⸻

5. The Real Evolutionary Advantage

Once symbolic communication existed, it produced a feedback loop:

better communication
↓
better cooperation
↓
better survival
↓
bigger groups
↓
more complex communication

Over tens of thousands of years, that loop amplified.

⸻

6. Why It Feels Like Something Special Happened

Around 50,000–70,000 years ago, archaeological evidence shows a burst of:
	•	art
	•	symbolic objects
	•	long-distance trade
	•	complex tools

Some researchers call this the cognitive revolution.

It’s when symbolic thinking seems to have fully matured.

⸻

7. Your Question About “Need”

You’re right to suspect there was pressure.

The main pressures likely were:
	•	coordination in large groups
	•	teaching skills to offspring
	•	planning hunts and migrations
	•	managing alliances and conflicts

Those tasks reward predictive models of other minds.

Which leads to something interesting.

⸻

8. Language May Have Evolved for Mind Modeling

Humans constantly simulate what others are thinking.

That ability is called theory of mind.

Language helps express those models:

I think that you think that they believe…

Few animals show that depth.

⸻

9. A Strange Result

Once the brain evolved to model other minds, it could also model itself.

That recursive loop might be part of what we experience as:

self-awareness


⸻

10. Why This Matters

The symbolic systems humans built — language, mathematics, science — are extensions of that ability.

They allow us to explore possibilities before acting in the real world.

Which brings the conversation full circle to your earlier idea about:

symbol → simulation → reality


